description.narrative: UNICEF Chile intensified its support to SENAME to prevent family separation and reduce institutionalization of children. UNICEF Chile developed a set of standards for the legal representation and defense of children in alternative care, and undertook a comprehensive study on the trajectory of adolescents within the juvenile justice system for the past 11 years. A Memorandum of Understanding was signed with the Supreme Court of Justice to develop criteria and procedures to determine and apply the best interest of the child in judicial decisions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/02/2020
